# Cloudflare Pages — legacy URL redirects (single-hop guarantee)
#
# GOAL: Every legacy path (no /en/ or /ar/ prefix) reaches its FINAL URL in ONE 301.
# Final form = absolute URL, locale prefix /en/, trailing slash (matches trailingSlash: true).
#
# Rules:
#   • Targets use https://kitzos.com/en/.../  so Next.js never adds a second trailing-slash hop.
#   • No rule targets a URL that itself redirects (all destinations are 200 on curl -sI).
#   • /ar/... paths are NOT listed — Arabic is served directly from the sitemap.
#   • / is NOT redirected here (favicon + canonical for crawlers; user redirect via JS in app/page.tsx).
#
# After deploy, each legacy URL below: 1× 301 → 200 (over HTTPS).
# Note: http:// requests still get a separate Always Use HTTPS hop first (Cloudflare dashboard).

# jpg-to-pdf merged into pdf-to-jpg (301, single-hop)
/en/tools/jpg-to-pdf    https://kitzos.com/en/tools/pdf-to-jpg/    301
/en/tools/jpg-to-pdf/   https://kitzos.com/en/tools/pdf-to-jpg/    301
/ar/tools/jpg-to-pdf    https://kitzos.com/ar/tools/pdf-to-jpg/    301
/ar/tools/jpg-to-pdf/   https://kitzos.com/ar/tools/pdf-to-jpg/    301

